# 2026-06-23 — Staging deploy incident notes

## Provisioning gap: REDIS_URL not set on school-kit-api

**Symptom:** API logs show `ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:6379` — the BullMQ / Redis
client is falling back to localhost because `REDIS_URL` is not set as a Fly
secret on the `school-kit-api` app.

**This is a provisioning gap, not a code bug.**

**Fix — run once before the next deploy attempt:**

```bash
flyctl secrets set \
  REDIS_URL="<Fly Redis private URL from flyctl redis list>" \
  --app school-kit-api
```

The Fly Redis private URL is the `.internal` form printed when the Redis
instance was created (`flyctl redis create`). Run `flyctl redis list` to
retrieve it if it was not noted at creation time.

The render worker (`school-kit-render-worker`) needs the same secret — set it
there too:

```bash
flyctl secrets set \
  REDIS_URL="<same Fly Redis private URL>" \
  --app school-kit-render-worker
```

Setting a Fly secret triggers a machine restart automatically; no manual redeploy
needed after `flyctl secrets set`.

## Also fixed in this session

- `fix/prisma-binary-target` (PR #64): strip non-Bookworm Prisma binaries before
  `pnpm deploy`; add `libssl3` to the API runtime stage. Root cause: `pnpm deploy
  --prod` was copying the `debian-openssl-1.1.x` query engine alongside the
  correct `debian-openssl-3.0.x` one; at runtime the wrong binary was loaded,
  producing `libssl.so.1.1: cannot open shared object file`.
